cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SE. 

The paper focuses on designing and implementing a decentralized replicated relational database with blockchain properties, which involves concepts from database systems (relational databases, transactions, consistency) and blockchain (decentralized consensus, trust model). Therefore, cs.DB (Database Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of serializable snapshot isolation (SSI) and consensus algorithms, which are relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The implementation aspect of the paper falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering), and the performance experiments involve analyzing the scalability and efficiency of the system, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
